-- Philippine Stock Movers: DFNN, Lepanto, Manila Mining, Omico
-- B y   N o r m a n   P .   A q u i n o
-- 2011-12-29T05:43:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/dfnn-pal-holdings-san-miguel-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (PCOMP)  moves in  Philippine (PASHR)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index increased 0.8 percent
to 4,371.96, the biggest gain in almost a month. The measure
advanced 4.1 percent this year, the third consecutive yearly
gain.  Mining shares:  Oriental Petroleum & Minerals Corp.  (OPM PM)
dropped 5.9 percent to 1.6 centavos, leading a decline among
Philippine mining companies after a gauge of six metals traded
on the London Metal Exchange including copper and nickel fell
2.2 percent yesterday, the sharpest loss since Dec. 14.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s biggest metal
producer, sank 2.1 percent to 20.85 pesos, the lowest close in
two weeks.  Manila Mining Corp. (MAB)  Class-B shares (MAB PM), which
are open to overseas investors, decreased 1.7 percent to 5.9
centavos and  Omico Corp. (OM)   slid 1.4 percent to 72
centavos.  Lepanto Consolidated Mining Co. (LC)   decreased 1.3
percent to 1.55 pesos, the lowest level since Nov. 29.  DFNN Inc. (DFNN)   rose 1.6 percent to 5.90 pesos, the
highest close in a week, after the Manila-based provider of
Internet-based stock-market investing services said it’s seeking
to double sales next year as it consolidates its gaming
business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
